n used in combination with [misoprostol] to prevent NSAID-induced gastric ulcers. Diclofenac was first approved by the FDA in July 1988 under the trade name Voltaren, marketed by Novartis (previously Ciba-Geigy).[L7360]','["S01CC01", "S01BC03", "M01AB55", "M02AA15", "M01AB05", "D11AX18"]','[]'),(20356,'Aaa','ششش','23','','','','','Unknown','غير محدد','','1','','','','',754,'2022-12-04',0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(20358,'Ginkoravia 80mg 20capsules','جينكورافيا 80مجم 20 كبسولة','110','90','Dietary supplement','Dietary supplement','Nutravia','Capsule','كبسولة','80mg','2','','','','',3101,'2025-06-17',0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL),(20359,'Adapalene duo forte gel 30 gm','ادابالين ديو فورت جل 30 جرام','79','','Anti-acne','Adapalene','Borg','Gel','جل','30 gm','1','','','','',1264,'2024-07-15',0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,0,'Acne vulgaris is a multifactorial disorder of the pilosebaceous unit involving increased sebum production, inflammation, and hyperproliferation/hyperkeratinization of the follicular infundibulum. It is also associated with _Cutibacterium acnes_ (also known as _Propionibacterium acnes_). Adapalene is a third-generation topical retinoid used for the treatment of acne vulgaris.[A193518] Adapalene has similar efficacy but a superior safety profile compared to tretinoin.[A193521] [Tazarotene] is more efficacious than adapalene but is designated as pregnancy category X and hence is contraindicated in pregnant women.[A193518] Adapalene can also be combined with benzoyl peroxide (BPO), which possesses bactericidal properties[A193524], and either adapalene alone, or adapalene BPO combination products, are commonly used to treat mild-to-severe acne.[A193518]

